{"word":"H5377 - נָשָׁא - nâshâʼ - naw-shaw' - Beguile","slug":"H5377","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָשָׁא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâshâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-shaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beguile"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D0; - na&#x0302;sha&#x0302;'</b> - <i>naw-shaw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>lead astray</i>, that is, (mentally) to <i>delude</i>, or (morally) to <i>seduce: - </i>beguile, deceive, X greatly, X utterly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4860\">H4860</a>, <a href=\"#/H4876\">H4876</a>"}]}